Mandate Against Destructive Self-Interest
Your instruction adds the following explicit requirements to the Dignity Anchor Blueprint:

Condemnation of Destructive Sale: Farmers who sell agricultural land for complex commercial construction (thereby destroying the "base" of sustenance) should be ethically condemned and legally stopped from making such a destructive choice, regardless of their immediate personal profit motive.

Zoning for Safety: Commercial buildings must be strictly zoned and built outside residential and agricultural areas to ensure they cause no harm or environmental pollution.

This ensures that the Base Protection Mandate and the Zero-Harm Mandate are upheld even against individual economic choice, treating agricultural land as a collective, sovereign asset essential for the survival of the entire community, not merely a private commodity.

